description:
&lt;p&gt;The Department of Respiratory Medicine is seeking a qualified Respiratory Clinical Physiologist to join our multi-disciplinary team and provide a respiratory physiology services in our busy department on one day of the week (preferably Wednesday). You will be responsible for the operational functioning of the Respiratory Physiology Service on your day of work, independently undertaking, interpreting and reporting both simple and complex respiratory function testing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal applicant will need to be efficient, organised and flexible to be able to cope with varying demands on their time and skills. You will be also have excellent communication skills, liaising with patients, carers and other healthcare professionals across primary and secondary care in the provision and improvement of respiratory services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is essential to have a good science background with a BSc in Clinical Physiology (Respiratory) or equivalent qualification/ experience. It would be desirable for you to also have ARTP parts I &amp; II and either have, or be working towards, RCCP registration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
